						<div class="postbody">I also forgot that OAM data readback isn't reliable, however this shouldn't matter on PAL NES as the OAM bytes 0-31 seem to be stable (based on blargg's earlier tests). It might produce strange results on NTSC NES though, depending on CPU-PPU synchronization. Can anybody try it out?</div>

					
